HEADWORD: Leaf-nosed
<hw>Leaf"-nosed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having a leaflike membrane on the nose; -- said of certain bats,
esp. of the genera <gen>Phyllostoma</gen> and <gen>Rhinonycteris</gen>.
See <er>Vampire</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

